H0.text: Absorption is a way that protists can obtain food besides ingesting and photosynthesis.

H1.text: Digestion is how protists can obtain food besides ingesting and photosynthesis.

H2.text: Accumulation is a way protists can obtain food besides ingesting and photosynthesis.

H3.text: Osmosis is a method by which protists obtain their food besides ingesting and photosynthesis.

A4.text: A phagosome is a vacuole formed around a particle absorbed by phagocytosis.

A5.text: A phagosome is a cellular compartment in which pathogenic microorganisms can be killed and digested.

A6.text: Osmosis provides the primary means by which water is transported into and out of cells.

A7.text: Phagocytosis is used by many protists as a means of feeding, thus constituting phagotrophy.
